1. Check that the container engine is installed
Open a terminal and run:
*  docker --version  *

2. Run an Nginx container
docker run -d --name nginx-container nginx:latest

3. List running containers
docker ps

4. Run an Ubuntu container attached to your terminal
docker run -it --name ubuntu-container ubuntu:latest

Ctrl + P, then Ctrl + Q -to exit for ubuntu terminal 

5. List containers again
docker ps

If you instead typed exit inside Ubuntu, the Ubuntu container would stop because its main command (bash) ended.
In that case, use this command to view both running and stopped containers:
docker ps -a

6. Stop the containers
docker stop nginx-container ubuntu-container

7. Remove the containers
docker rm nginx-container ubuntu-container

Easy-peasy!
